definition: to intercept at the net (volleyball, tennis etc)/(computing) to seal off a network
to confer/to grant/to bestow a title/to seal/classifier for sealed objects, esp. letters

sentences.english: No timetable was given by the government for the speed with which the process can go from a warning letter to internet suspension.
sentences.chinese: 政府沒有給出從警告信到封網具體需要多少時間。

sentences.english: As the American debate intensifies, Chinese officials misrepresent the extent of Internet filtering.
sentences.chinese: 隨着美國的爭論加劇，中國官員試圖掩飾封網的規模。
